(E) ΔV1/2 in the absence (hollow bars) or presence (solid bars) of 2 M sucrose. Hatched bar indicates ΔV1/2 in the presence of 2 M urea or 9 M glycerol. Asterisks indicate a significant difference (p < 0.05 in student’s t test) of ΔV1/2 resulted from 2 M sucrose or 9 M glycerol. (F) ΔΔV1/2 caused by sucrose. ΔΔV1/2 = ΔV1/22 M sucrose - ΔV1/20 sucrose. Hatched bar indicates ΔΔV1/2 caused by 2 M urea or 9 M glycerol. The dashed lines give the 99% confidence interval for ΔΔV1/2 of WT.

